{{wiktionary|daisy cutter}} '''Daisy cutter''' may refer to:
* [[Daisy cutter (fuse)]], a type of fuse designed to detonate an aerial bomb at or above ground level * [[BLU-82]], a type of bomb nicknamed Daisy Cutter in Vietnam * In [[Glossary of cricket terms#D|cricket]], a ball that bounces multiple times before reaching the batsman * A seldom used term for a sharply struck ground ball in baseball, used mostly in [[Vintage base ball#Glossary|Vintage base ball]] * A song on the album ''[[Uplifter]]'' by 311 * A pale ale brewed by [[Half Acre Beer Company]] of Chicago, Illinois
